32	sessionId = 3a0546c8-a78f-4336-bec2-8f3a2bcd45b6	{"type": "ai", "content": "Sure! Here's a delicious recipe for crispy fried chicken:\\n\\n### Crispy Fried Chicken Recipe\\n\\n#### Ingredients\\n\\n**For the Chicken:**\\n- 4 lbs chicken pieces (legs, thighs, wings, or breasts)\\n- 2 cups buttermilk (or milk with 1 tablespoon of lemon juice)\\n- 1 tablespoon hot sauce (optional)\\n- Salt and pepper (to taste)\\n\\n**For the Coating:**\\n- 2 cups all-purpose flour\\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\\n- 1 teaspoon onion powder\\n- 1 teaspoon paprika\\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\\n- Salt and pepper (to taste)\\n  \\n**For Frying:**\\n- Vegetable oil (for frying)\\n\\n#### Instructions\\n\\n1. **Marinate the Chicken:**\\n   - In a large bowl, combine the buttermilk, hot sauce (if using), salt, and pepper. \\n   - Add the chicken pieces, making sure they're well-coated. \\n   - Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.\\n\\n2. **Prepare the Coating:**\\n   - In a large bowl or shallow dish, mix together the flour, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, baking powder, salt, and pepper.\\n\\n3. **Dredge the Chicken:**\\n   - Remove the chicken from the buttermilk, allowing excess to drip off.\\n   - Dredge each piece in the flour mixture, pressing firmly to ensure a good coating. Shake off any excess flour.\\n\\n4. **Heat the Oil:**\\n   - In a large, heavy skillet or deep fryer, heat about 2 inches of vegetable oil to 350°F (175°C). \\n   - Use a thermometer to monitor the temperature for consistent frying.\\n\\n5. **Fry the Chicken:**\\n   - Working in batches, carefully add the chicken pieces to the hot oil. Do not overcrowd the pan.\\n   - Fry for about 10-15 minutes on each side, or until the chicken is golden brown and cooked through (internal temperature should reach 165°F or 75°C).\\n   \\n6. **Drain:**\\n   - Remove the chicken from the oil and place it on a wire rack or paper towels to drain excess oil.\\n\\n7. **Serve:**\\n   - Allow the chicken to rest for a few minutes before serving. Enjoy with your favorite sides!\\n\\n### Tips:\\n- For extra crunch, you can double-dip the chicken by dipping it back in the buttermilk and then again in the flour mixture.\\n- Consider adding spices to the flour for extra flavor (like cayenne pepper for heat or herbs for freshness).\\n\\nEnjoy your crispy fried chicken!", "tool_calls": [], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "invalid_tool_calls": []}
