36	sessionId = 3a0546c8-a78f-4336-bec2-8f3a2bcd45b6	{"type": "ai", "content": "Great choice! Here’s how to make your crispy fried chicken spicy:\\n\\n### Spicy Crispy Fried Chicken Recipe\\n\\n#### Ingredients\\n\\n**For the Chicken:**\\n- 4 lbs chicken pieces (legs, thighs, wings, or breasts)\\n- 2 cups buttermilk (or milk with 1 tablespoon lemon juice)\\n- 2 tablespoons hot sauce (adjust according to your spice preference; use your favorite brand)\\n- 1-2 teaspoons cayenne pepper (or more, depending on how spicy you want it)\\n- Salt and pepper (to taste)\\n\\n**For the Coating:**\\n- 2 cups all-purpose flour\\n- 1 teaspoon garlic powder\\n- 1 teaspoon onion powder\\n- 1 teaspoon paprika (smoked paprika adds extra flavor)\\n- 1-2 teaspoons cayenne pepper (optional for extra heat)\\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\\n- Salt and pepper (to taste)\\n\\n**For Frying:**\\n- Vegetable oil (for frying)\\n\\n#### Instructions\\n\\n1. **Marinate the Chicken:**\\n   - In a large bowl, combine the buttermilk, hot sauce, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper.\\n   - Add the chicken pieces, ensuring they are well-coated. \\n   - Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, preferably overnight.\\n\\n2. **Prepare the Coating:**\\n   - In another bowl or shallow dish, mix together the flour, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, baking powder, and cayenne pepper (if using). Add salt and pepper to taste.\\n\\n3. **Dredge the Chicken:**\\n   - Remove the chicken from the buttermilk, letting the excess drip off.\\n   - Dredge each piece in the flour mixture, pressing firmly to ensure a good coating. Shake off any excess flour.\\n\\n4. **Heat the Oil:**\\n   - In a large skillet or deep fryer, heat about 2 inches of vegetable oil to 350°F (175°C).\\n\\n5. **Fry the Chicken:**\\n   - Carefully add the chicken pieces in batches, being careful not to overcrowd the pan.\\n   - Fry for about 10-15 minutes on each side or until golden brown and the internal temperature reaches 165°F (75°C).\\n\\n6. **Drain:**\\n   - Remove the chicken and place it on a wire rack or paper towels to drain excess oil.\\n\\n7. **Serve:**\\n   - Let the chicken rest for a few minutes before serving. Consider adding a sprinkle of your favorite hot seasoning or extra cayenne on top for a finishing touch.\\n\\n### Tips for Extra Spice:\\n- For a more intense flavor, consider adding crushed red pepper flakes to the buttermilk marinade or the flour mixture.\\n- Serve with spicy dipping sauces like sriracha, buffalo sauce, or a spicy aioli for an extra kick.\\n\\nEnjoy your spicy crispy fried chicken!", "tool_calls": [], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "invalid_tool_calls": []}
