112	sessionId = 102.220.210.182	{"type": "ai", "content": "Here are your saved recipes:\\n\\n1. **Spicy Blue Cheese Sauce**\\n   - **Ingredients**: \\n     - 1/2 cup crumbled blue cheese\\n     - 1/4 cup sour cream\\n     - 1/4 cup mayonnaise\\n     - 1 tablespoon lemon juice\\n     - 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\\n     - 1-2 tablespoons hot sauce\\n     - Salt and pepper to taste\\n   - **Instructions**:\\n     1. In a bowl, combine blue cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, and lemon juice.\\n     2. Mix until well blended but still chunky.\\n     3. Add garlic powder, hot sauce, salt, and pepper to taste.\\n     4. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.\\n\\n2. **Blue Cheese Sauce**\\n   - **Ingredients**: \\n     - 1/2 cup crumbled blue cheese\\n     - 1/4 cup sour cream\\n     - 1/4 cup mayonnaise\\n     - 1 tablespoon lemon juice\\n     - 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\\n     - Salt and pepper to taste\\n   - **Instructions**:\\n     1. In a bowl, combine blue cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, and lemon juice.\\n     2. Mix until well blended but still chunky.\\n     3. Add garlic powder, salt, and pepper to taste.\\n     4. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving.\\n\\n3. **Crispy Chicken Wings**\\n   - **Ingredients**: \\n     - 2 pounds chicken wings\\n     - 1 tablespoon baking powder\\n     - 1 teaspoon salt\\n     - 1/2 teaspoon black pepper\\n     - 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\\n     - 1/2 teaspoon paprika\\n     - Oil for frying\\n   - **Instructions**:\\n     1. Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).\\n     2. Pat the chicken wings dry with paper towels.\\n     3. In a bowl, toss chicken wings with baking powder, salt, pepper, garlic powder, and paprika.\\n     4. Arrange wings on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.\\n     5. Bake for 40-45 minutes, flipping halfway through, until crispy.\\n\\n4. **Buffalo Hot Sauce**\\n   - **Ingredients**: \\n     - 1 cup hot sauce\\n     - 1/2 cup unsalted butter\\n     - 1 tablespoon white vinegar\\n     - 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce\\n     - 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder\\n     - Salt to taste\\n   - **Instructions**:\\n     1. Melt the butter in a saucepan over low heat.\\n     2. Mix in hot sauce, white vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, and garlic powder.\\n     3. Whisk until fully blended and warmed.\\n     4. Season with salt as desired.\\n\\n5. **Classic Apple Pie**\\n   - **Ingredients**: \\n     - 2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\\n     - 1 teaspoon salt\\n     - 1 teaspoon sugar\\n     - 1 cup unsalted butter, chilled and diced\\n     - 6 to 8 tablespoons ice water\\n     - 6 to 8 apples, peeled, cored, and sliced\\n     - 3/4 cup sugar\\n     - 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour\\n     - 1 teaspoon cinnamon\\n     - 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg\\n     - 1 tablespoon lemon juice\\n     - 1 tablespoon butter\\n   - **Instructions**:\\n     1. Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).\\n     2. In a bowl, combine flour, salt, and sugar.\\n     3. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.\\n     4. Stir in ice water until mixture forms a ball. Refrigerate.\\n     5. Prepare apple mixture and assemble the pie. Bake.\\n\\n6. **High Protein Cottage Cheese Bowl**\\n   - **Ingredients**: \\n     - 1 cup cottage cheese\\n     - 1/2 cup sliced peaches\\n     - 1/4 cup walnuts\\n     - 1 tablespoon honey\\n     - 1 tablespoon cinnamon\\n   - **Instructions**:\\n     1. In a bowl, scoop the cottage cheese.\\n     2. Top with sliced peaches, walnuts, honey, and sprinkle with cinnamon.\\n     3. Mix gently and enjoy.\\n\\n7. **High Protein Egg and Quinoa Bowl**\\n   - **Ingredients**: \\n     - 1 cup cooked quinoa\\n     - 2 large eggs\\n     - 1/2 avocado, sliced\\n     - 1/4 cup black beans\\n     - 1/4 cup diced tomatoes\\n     - Salt and pepper to taste\\n     - Olive oil for cooking\\n   - **Instructions**:\\n     1. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.\\n     2. Scramble the eggs until fully cooked.\\n     3. Combine all ingredients in a bowl and serve warm.\\n\\n8. **High Protein Smoothie**\\n   - **Ingredients**: \\n     - 1 cup spinach\\n     - 1 banana\\n     - 1 cup Greek yogurt\\n     - 1 scoop protein powder\\n     - 1 tablespoon peanut butter\\n     - 1 cup almond milk\\n   - **Instructions**:\\n     1. Blend all ingredients until smooth.\\n     2. Pour into a glass and enjoy.\\n\\nIf you want to view or delete any specific recipe, let me know!", "tool_calls": [], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "invalid_tool_calls": []}
