138	sessionId = 	{"type": "ai", "content": "Here are your saved recipes:\\n\\n### 1. Spicy Blue Cheese Sauce\\n- **Ingredients:**\\n  - 1/2 cup crumbled blue cheese\\n  - 1/4 cup sour cream\\n  - 1/4 cup mayonnaise\\n  - 1 tablespoon lemon juice\\n  - 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\\n  - 1-2 tablespoons hot sauce\\n  - Salt and pepper to taste\\n- **Instructions:**\\n  1. In a bowl, combine blue cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, and lemon juice.\\n  2. Mix until well blended but still chunky.\\n  3. Add garlic powder, hot sauce, salt, and pepper to taste.\\n  4. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes before serving to allow flavors to meld.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. Blue Cheese Sauce\\n- **Ingredients:**\\n  - 1/2 cup crumbled blue cheese\\n  - 1/4 cup sour cream\\n  - 1/4 cup mayonnaise\\n  - 1 tablespoon lemon juice\\n  - 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder\\n  - Salt and pepper to taste\\n- **Instructions:**\\n  1. In a bowl, combine blue cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise, and lemon juice.\\n  2. Mix until well blended but still chunky.\\n  3. Add garlic powder, salt, and pepper to taste.\\n  4. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes for flavors to meld.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. Buffalo Hot Sauce\\n- **Ingredients:**\\n  - 1 cup hot sauce\\n  - 1/2 cup unsalted butter\\n  - 1 tablespoon white vinegar\\n  - 1 teaspoon Worcestershire sauce\\n  - 1/4 teaspoon garlic powder\\n  - Salt to taste\\n- **Instructions:**\\n  1. Melt the butter in a saucepan over low heat.\\n  2. Mix in hot sauce, white vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, and garlic powder.\\n  3. Whisk until blended and warmed.\\n  4. Season with salt as needed and serve or store in an airtight container.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. Classic Apple Pie\\n- **Ingredients:**\\n  - 2 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\\n  - 1 teaspoon salt\\n  - 1 teaspoon sugar\\n  - 1 cup unsalted butter, chilled and diced\\n  - 6 to 8 tablespoons ice water\\n  - 6 to 8 apples, peeled and sliced\\n  - 3/4 cup sugar\\n  - 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour\\n  - 1 teaspoon cinnamon\\n  - 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg\\n  - 1 tablespoon lemon juice\\n  - 1 tablespoon butter\\n- **Instructions:**\\n  1. Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).\\n  2. Combine flour, salt, and sugar in a bowl.\\n  3. Cut in butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.\\n  4. Stir in ice water until a ball forms; wrap in plastic and refrigerate.\\n  5. Roll out one disc and fit into the pie pan.\\n  6. Toss apples with sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, and lemon juice; fill crust.\\n  7. Roll out second disc, cover filling, seal edges, cut slits for ventilation.\\n  8. Bake for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350°F (175°C) and bake for 35-45 minutes until golden.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. High Protein Cottage Cheese Bowl\\n- **Ingredients:**\\n  - 1 cup cottage cheese\\n  - 1/2 cup sliced peaches\\n  - 1/4 cup walnuts\\n  - 1 tablespoon honey\\n  - 1 tablespoon cinnamon\\n- **Instructions:**\\n  1. In a bowl, scoop the cottage cheese.\\n  2. Top with sliced peaches, walnuts, honey, and sprinkle cinnamon.\\n  3. Mix gently and enjoy.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 6. High Protein Egg and Quinoa Bowl\\n- **Ingredients:**\\n  - 1 cup cooked quinoa\\n  - 2 large eggs\\n  - 1/2 avocado, sliced\\n  - 1/4 cup black beans\\n  - 1/4 cup diced tomatoes\\n  - Salt and pepper to taste\\n  - Olive oil for cooking\\n- **Instructions:**\\n  1. Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat; scramble eggs.\\n  2. Combine quinoa, eggs, black beans, and tomatoes in a bowl.\\n  3. Top with avocado and season with salt and pepper. Serve warm.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 7. High Protein Smoothie\\n- **Ingredients:**\\n  - 1 cup spinach\\n  - 1 banana\\n  - 1 cup Greek yogurt\\n  - 1 scoop protein powder\\n  - 1 tablespoon peanut butter\\n  - 1 cup almond milk\\n- **Instructions:**\\n  1. Blend all ingredients until smooth and enjoy.\\n\\n---\\n\\nLet me know if you need any more help!", "tool_calls": [], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "invalid_tool_calls": []}
