poon salt\\",\\"1 teaspoon sugar\\",\\"1 cup unsalted butter, chilled and diced\\",\\"6 to 8 tablespoons ice water\\",\\"6 to 8 apples, peeled, cored, and sliced\\",\\"3/4 cup sugar\\",\\"2 tablespoons all-purpose flour\\",\\"1 teaspoon cinnamon\\",\\"1/4 teaspoon nutmeg\\",\\"1 tablespoon lemon juice\\",\\"1 tablespoon butter\\"],\\"instructions\\":[\\"Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).\\",\\"In a bowl, combine flour, salt, and sugar.\\",\\"Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.\\",\\"Stir in ice water, a tablespoon at a time, until mixture forms a ball.\\",\\"Divide dough in half, shape into discs, wrap in plastic, and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.\\",\\"Roll out one disc to fit the pie pan and place in the pan.\\",\\"In a large bowl, toss sliced apples with sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, and lemon juice.\\",\\"Fill the pie crust with the apple mixture and dot with butter.\\",\\"Roll out the second disc, place over the filling, seal edges, and cut slits for ventilation.\\",\\"Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes, reduce temperature to 350°F (175°C), and continue baking for 35 to 45 minutes until apples are soft and crust is golden brown.\\"],\\"created_at\\":\\"2026-03-05T09:46:23.905806\\"},{\\"id\\":9,\\"title\\":\\"High Protein Cottage Cheese Bowl\\",\\"ingredients\\":[\\"1 cup cottage cheese\\",\\"1/2 cup sliced peaches\\",\\"1/4 cup walnuts\\",\\"1 tablespoon honey\\",\\"1 tablespoon cinnamon\\"],\\"instructions\\":[\\"In a bowl, scoop the cottage cheese.\\",\\"Top with sliced peaches, walnuts, honey, and sprinkle with cinnamon.\\",\\"Mix gently and enjoy.\\"],\\"created_at\\":\\"2026-03-05T09:20:10.830511\\"},{\\"id\\":6,\\"title\\":\\"High Protein Egg and Quinoa Bowl\\",\\"ingredients\\":[\\"1 cup cooked quinoa\\",\\"2 large eggs\\",\\"1/2 avocado, sliced\\",\\"1/4 cup black beans\\",\\"1/4 cup diced tomatoes\\",\\"Salt and pepper to taste\\",\\"Olive oil for cooking\\"],\\"instructions\\":[\\"Heat olive oil in a skillet over medium heat.\\",\\"Scramble the eggs until fully cooked.\\",\\"In a bowl, combine cooked quinoa, scrambled eggs, black beans, and diced tomatoes.\\",\\"Top with sliced avocado and season with salt and pepper.\\",\\"Serve warm.\\"],\\"created_at\\":\\"2026-03-04T15:42:23.870087\\"},{\\"id\\":5,\\"title\\":\\"High Protein Smoothie\\",\\"ingredients\\":[\\"1 cup spinach\\",\\"1 banana\\",\\"1 cup Greek yogurt\\",\\"1 scoop protein powder\\",\\"1 tablespoon peanut butter\\",\\"1 cup almond milk\\"],\\"instructions\\":[\\"Combine spinach, banana, Greek yogurt, protein powder, peanut butter, and almond milk in a blender.\\",\\"Blend until smooth.\\",\\"Pour into a glass and enjoy.\\"],\\"created_at\\":\\"2026-03-04T15:38:08.859035\\"}]", "tool_call_id": "call_tEp5eaP7RBFfZVVdiCylThH3", "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}}
146	sessionId = 102.220.210.182	{"type": "ai", "content": "It looks like I couldn't find a chocolate cake recipe in your saved recipes. However, I can help you by guiding you to a simple chocolate cake recipe:\\n\\n### Chocolate Cake Recipe\\n\\n#### Ingredients:\\n- **1 and 3/4 cups all-purpose flour**\\n- **3/4 cup unsweetened cocoa powder**\\n- **2 cups sugar**\\n- **1 and 1/2 teaspoons baking powder**\\n- **1 and 1/2 teaspoons baking soda**\\n- **1 teaspoon salt**\\n- **2 large eggs**\\n- **1 cup whole milk**\\n- **1/2 cup vegetable oil**\\n- **2 teaspoons vanilla extract**\\n- **1 cup boiling water**\\n\\n#### Instructions:\\n1. **Preheat Oven**: Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C). Grease and flour two 9-inch round baking pans.\\n  \\n2. **Mix Dry Ingredients**: In a large bowl, whisk together the flour, cocoa powder, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.\\n\\n3. **Add Wet Ingredients**: Add the eggs, milk, oil, and vanilla to the dry ingredients. Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes. \\n\\n4. **Add Boiling Water**: Stir in the boiling water (the batter will be thin). Pour the batter evenly into the prepared pans.\\n\\n5. **Bake**: Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. \\n\\n6. **Cool**: Allow to cool for 10 minutes, then remove from pans to cool completely on a wire rack.\\n\\n7. **Frosting (Optional)**: You can frost the cake with your favorite chocolate frosting once it has cooled.\\n\\nFeel free to let me know if you'd like me to search for specific recipes or help in any other way!", "tool_calls": [], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "invalid_tool_calls": []}
