176	sessionId = 41.193.212.95	{"type": "ai", "content": "I have created and saved the **Tangy Mushroom Sauce** recipe for you! Here are the details:\\n\\n### Tangy Mushroom Sauce\\n\\n**Ingredients:**\\n- 500g mushrooms, sliced\\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\\n- 1 onion, finely chopped\\n- 2 garlic cloves, minced\\n- 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce\\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\\n- 1 tablespoon lemon juice\\n- 1 cup vegetable broth\\n- 1 tablespoon cornstarch (mixed with 2 tablespoons water)\\n- Salt and pepper to taste\\n- Fresh parsley, chopped (for garnish)\\n\\n**Instructions:**\\n1. In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add chopped onion and garlic, sauté until translucent.\\n2. Add the sliced mushrooms and cook until they are golden brown, about 5-7 minutes.\\n3. Stir in Worcestershire sauce, soy sauce, and lemon juice, mixing well.\\n4. Add vegetable broth and bring to a simmer. Cook for 5 minutes.\\n5. Slowly stir in the cornstarch mixture to thicken the sauce, cooking for another 2-3 minutes until it reaches your desired consistency.\\n6. Season with salt and pepper to taste.\\n7. Serve warm, garnished with chopped parsley.\\n\\nEnjoy your cooking! 🍄✨", "tool_calls": [], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "invalid_tool_calls": []}
